        <div type="edition">
            <ab>
                <lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>acrum</ex></expan>.
                <lb n="2"/><persName><name type="gentilicium" key="Aponia">Aponiae</name> <name type="cognomen" key="Lochias">Lochiadi</name></persName>.
                <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>V</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>a</abbr><ex>nnis</ex></expan> <num value="26">XXVI</num>.
                <lb n="4"/><persName><name type="cognomen" key="Fructus">Fructus</name></persName> frater e<hi rend="tall">t</hi>
                <lb n="5"/><persName><name type="cognomen" key="Nicephor">Nicephor</name></persName> coniugi
                <lb n="6"/>optimae et
                <lb n="7"/>p<hi rend="tall">i</hi>issimae.
            </ab>
                <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->

            </div>


                <div type="translation">
                    <p>Sacred to the Divine Spirits. To Aponia Lochias. She lived for twenty-six
               years. Fructus, (her) brother, and Nicephor, for the best and most dutiful wife,
               (made this).</p>
                </div>



                <div type="commentary">
                    <p>In line 7, the tall “i” of piissimae is probably decorative, as it should
               preclude the presence of another “i.” </p>
                </div>



